Class SignalResponseProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.agilewiki.jactor2.core.messages.SignalResponseProcessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AsyncResponseProcessor<java.lang.Void>

    public final class SignalResponseProcessor
extends java.lang.Object
implements AsyncResponseProcessor<java.lang.Void>
    Used to flag a message as a 1-way message. The singleton serves as a flag, so no response is ever returned and consequently the processAsyncResponse method should never actually be invoked.

      • processAsyncResponse

        public void processAsyncResponse(java.lang.Void response)
        Description copied from interface: AsyncResponseProcessor
        The processAsyncResponse method accepts the response of a request.

        This method need not be thread-safe, as it is always invoked from the same light-weight thread (targetReactor) that passed the AsyncRequest and AsyncResponseProcessor objects.
